rComments: Good Prof, I had him for a grad course which was not listed in the options above. He has excellent diction and explains concepts very well. He is a bit intimidating and his assignments are exceptionally difficult though.

He uses the exact same lecture notes and problem sets for his graduate quantum mechanics course. His notes are very organized, and he is happy to answer questions. However, he might appear quite emotionless and cold, and smile strangely, so one may feel intimidated. His exam was based closely on homework.

His exams are brutal. We had to do a remake because the class average was ~20%. He doesn't seem to really care about anything. It appears he would rather spend his time on research rather than teaching.
only 2 people passed the midterm he gave....bloody tough exams
Sajeev is an emotionless robot.  Instead of coffee in his mug, he takes pure oil, black as the night.
